    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for Model Risk 3. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged; however, the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%), the use of production-representative hardware across two independent laboratories, and the robustness of input characterization provide sufficient overall credibility to support the regulatory decision. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for the stated COU.",
